How enterprise Linux is developed?
1. The most recent versions as well as new Experimental Packages are combined into distribution called Fedora.
    Fedora Project was created by the Red Hat Corporation


In 2003 Red hat chose to split Red Hat Linux into 
    1. Red Hat enterprise Server - for Commercial Market
    2. Fedora Core - Individual

In Fedora, Software is downloaded by users, tested and bug fixed.
And when it reaches the sufficient level of stability, Red Hat Starts the next release of 
enterprise linux from those packages